---
import ContentLayout from '../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, GAME_NAME } from '../data/site';
---

<ContentLayout
  title="Editorial Policy"
  description="Editorial and testing policy for Demon Born Compass — how facts are verified."
  canonicalUrl="/editorial/"
>
  <h1>Editorial &amp; Testing Policy</h1>

  <p>
    <strong>{SITE_TITLE}</strong> is an evidence-backed, unofficial fan guide for {GAME_NAME} on Roblox.
    This page explains how facts are selected, verified, and published — and what this site will
    never claim.
  </p>

  <h2>Source hierarchy</h2>
  <p>Every published game fact must trace to one of the following, in priority order:</p>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Official Roblox API or game page</strong> — the Roblox Games API, official game description, or official creator channel.</li>
    <li><strong>Two or more independent community sources</strong> — only when official sources are unavailable, and only for orientation rather than specific numbers or mechanics.</li>
    <li><strong>Operator observation</strong> — noted as <em>community-reported</em> and subject to revision.</li>
  </ol>
  <p>No single third-party guide site, Reddit post, or YouTube video is sufficient on its own to establish a published fact.</p>

  <h2>What this site publishes</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Official controls listed on the Roblox game description page (source: DB-API-001)</li>
    <li>Official game scope and player route wording from the Roblox description (source: DB-API-001)</li>
    <li>Identity, creator, and genre metadata from the Roblox Games API (source: DB-API-001/002/003)</li>
    <li>SERP and trend gap observations from user-supplied screenshots (source: DB-SERP-001, DB-TRENDS-001)</li>
    <li>Wiki, Trello, and codes status pages that clearly state when no official source is confirmed</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What this site will not publish</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Codes copied from third-party sites</strong> — Pocket Tactics, Destructoid, Beebom, Radio Times, or any other code aggregator. Codes are only published when confirmed from an official Roblox channel or in-game redemption UI.</li>
    <li><strong>Tier lists or best build recommendations</strong> — no methodology or tested data exists yet.</li>
    <li><strong>Best clan, best breathing style, or blood demon arts guides</strong> — no official source confirms these mechanics yet.</li>
    <li><strong>Official Trello or Discord confirmation</strong> — unless a verified official Roblox or creator link is provided.</li>
    <li><strong>Unverified walkthroughs, boss guides, or quest steps</strong> — requires hands-on testing or official documentation.</li>
    <li><strong>Third-party screenshots or Roblox media</strong> — no image republication license has been verified.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Verification statuses used on this site</h2>
  <div class="table-wrapper">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Status</th>
          <th>Meaning</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>official-confirmed</code></td>
          <td>Fact verified against official Roblox API or game description</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>official-confirmed-limited</code></td>
          <td>Official sources confirm the broad scope but detailed steps/mechanics are unverified</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>volatile-snapshot</code></td>
          <td>Metric from Roblox API that may have changed since retrieval (e.g. player count, votes)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>serp-gap-confirmed</code></td>
          <td>SERP analysis shows no authoritative result exists for this query yet</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>unverified-official-link</code></td>
          <td>No official URL confirmed for this resource; third-party leads noted</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>source-limited</code></td>
          <td>Official source not yet available; page states what is needed before facts can be published</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2>No AI fabrication rule</h2>
  <p>
    No game fact, numeric value, version number, code, or mechanic is invented by AI.
    All published claims are either (a) extracted from registered official sources, or (b)
    marked with a status that clearly communicates they are unverified.
  </p>

  <h2>Updates and version changes</h2>
  <p>
    When Roblox publishes an update that changes a published fact, a new issue is created
    and the relevant page is flagged. Pages are not auto-corrected without human review.
  </p>
</ContentLayout>